# Git stores text files with LF and, on Windows with the default
# core.autocrlf=true, checks them back out with CRLF. That is invisible for
# source code and fatal for anything Linux executes.
#
# docker-entrypoint.sh is the case that bites: COPY carries the CRLF into the
# image, the kernel reads the shebang as `bash\r`, and the container dies with
#
#   env: 'bash\r': No such file or directory
#
# before running a single command. The failure only appears when the image is
# rebuilt from a Windows checkout, so it hides from whoever built the image
# first and hits everyone who clones afterwards.
#
# These files run inside containers. They keep LF on every platform.
*.sh text eol=lf
Dockerfile text eol=lf
.dockerignore text eol=lf
docker-compose.yml text eol=lf
